n and suggests a new model of local and regional interconnection in the third and second millennia B.C.E. Frachetti further argues that these early nomadic communities played a pivotal role in shaping enduring networks of exchange across Eurasia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAntiquities, PrehistoricxEurasia. 0aAntiquities, PrehistoriczEurasia. 0aBronze agexEurasia. 0aBronze agezEurasia. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)xEurasia. 0aExcavations (Archaeology)zEurasia. 0aPastoral systems, PrehistoricxEurasia. 0aPastoral systems, PrehistoriczEurasia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Archaeology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942691423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520942691.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles